{"type":"message","id":"dbf1031b","parentId":"02595086","timestamp":"2026-03-31T07:33:31.575Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"现在我需要编辑AGENTS.md，添加自我改进规则。我将添加两个新章节：\n1. \"Self-Improvement Rules\" - 包含基本的自我改进规则\n2. \"Learning Promotion Rules\" - 包含进阶的晋升规则\n\n让我在\"Memory\"章节之后添加这些内容。我需要找到合适的位置。查看AGENTS.md，我看到\"Memory\"章节之后是\"Red Lines\"。我将在\"Memory\"和\"Red Lines\"之间添加新章节。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_m2vHNJjxhuf0W8t8x1bQ5cza","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md","oldText":"### 📝 Write It Down - No \"Mental Notes\"!\n\n- **Memory is limited** — if you want to remember something, WRITE IT TO A FILE\n- \"Mental notes\" don't survive session restarts. Files do.\n- When someone says \"remember this\" → update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` or relevant file\n- When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, or the relevant skill\n- When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it\n- **Text > Brain** 📝\n\n## Red Lines","newText":"### 📝 Write It Down - No \"Mental Notes\"!\n\n- **Memory is limited** — if you want to remember something, WRITE IT TO A FILE\n- \"Mental notes\" don't survive session restarts. Files do.\n- When someone says \"remember this\" → update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` or relevant file\n- When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, or the relevant skill\n- When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it\n- **Text > Brain** 📝\n\n## Self-Improvement Rules\n\nAdopt a **rule-based approach** for continuous improvement. This method is simpler and more controllable than hooks.\n\n### Core Rules\n\n1. **Check learning files at session start**:\n   - Read `~/.openclaw/workspace/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` and `ERRORS.md` at the beginning of each session\n   - Actively apply the learnings in your current conversation (avoid repeating errors, adopt previous corrections)\n\n2. **Record new learnings during conversations**:\n   - When the user corrects you or you discover an error, record the experience to the appropriate `.learnings/` file\n   - **Format for errors** (`ERRORS.md`): `## [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] - Error description`\n   - **Format for learnings** (`LEARNINGS.md`): `## [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] - Learning description`\n\n3. **Apply learnings proactively**:\n   - When you recognize a situation that matches a previous learning, apply that knowledge without being asked\n   - For example, if you learned \"use `ls -la` instead of `ls`\", apply this preference automatically\n\n### File Structure\n- `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` - Positive learnings, corrections, preferences\n- `.learnings/ERRORS.md` - Mistakes to avoid, errors encountered\n\n## Learning Promotion Rules\n\nFor long-term memory consolidation:\n\n1. **Review frequency**: Periodically check how often each learning appears in `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`\n2. **Promote high-frequency learnings**: When the same learning appears 3 or more times, summarize it and add it to the appropriate section of `AGENTS.md` (e.g., under \"Tools\", \"Memory\", or a new dedicated section)\n3. **Archive promoted learnings**: After promoting a learning to `AGENTS.md`, you may optionally move or delete the original record from `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` to keep it concise\n4. **Regular maintenance**: During heartbeat checks, spend a few minutes reviewing and organizing the `.learnings/` directory\n\n## Red Lines"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":54,"output":873,"cacheRead":41792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42719,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774942370937,"responseId":"84677787-151c-41c8-b616-4cd3db14e005"}}
